html:
Shawn, I see your trial did not have a ton of activity. Is it early in your search?

The hundreds of boards I have worked with, all stress how difficult it is to get board material into the hands of everyone. I work on a committee, and we have 'digitally-duct taped' our own process, but we're all tech-savvy. Not all board members are. Less is best.

The three main reasons organizations switch over to using a board management solution is because they need help: 
1. Centralizing board material
2. Emails are getting out of hand
3. Engaging members outside of meetings
Does your organization need help in any of these areas? 

Brittany Florentine
Account Representative, Boardable 
317-689-0990

Check out our new Mobile App, available on both  iOS and  Android devices!

Hi Joanna,

My sincerest apologies, due to the experience with COVID-19 we are experiencing financial difficulties at this time and are awaiting government support in order to restore all operations.  If there is anything you can do in order to support during this time it would be greatly appreciated.  We are a 501(c)(3) United States Public Charity if it makes any difference.  Thanks for your understanding and I look forward to your response.

Best Regards,

/s/
Shawn

﻿
Hi, Shawn. 

I heard from our team that you're experiencing financial difficulties during the COVID-19 crisis. First, I'm really sorry to hear about your challenges. We understand is a very challenging of uncertainty and want to be a good partner while you navigate. 

How were you hoping we could help? Was there something specific you had in mind? 

If your board is continuing to meet virtual, we do have some virtual meeting tools which might also be helpful including a new videoconferencing feature that we are testing with some customers that we could offer free access to at the moment. 

Thanks again, 
Samantha
--

html:
Hi Shawn,

I hope you are doing well. I wanted to reach out to you regarding the Your 10 Life Boardable account. It looks like the credit card you have been using is no longer allowing the charge.

To resolve this, you can simply log into your Boardable account and go into the subscription page on the left side. There you can double-check the payment information.

If you need to make changes to your card, you can select "update credit card" under the Verify Credit Card section. This will allow you to enter your new card information. on a file and/or enter an updated credit card.

Please let me know if you have any questions or if I can be of any help. Thanks so much.

Take care,
Katie




Katie Cordell

Customer Success Manager |  Boardable

p. 317.689.0990

From: Brittany Florentine <brittany@boardable.com>
Sent: Tuesday, November 5, 2019 8:23 AM
To: Shawn Micheal <Shawn@Your10Life.com>
Subject: Were we not a good fit?
 
Shawn, I see your trial did not have a ton of activity. Is it early in your search?

The hundreds of boards I have worked with, all stress how difficult it is to get board material into the hands of everyone. I work on a committee, and we have 'digitally-duct taped' our own process, but we're all tech-savvy. Not all board members are. Less is best.

The three main reasons organizations switch over to using a board management solution is because they need help: 
1. Centralizing board material
2. Emails are getting out of hand
3. Engaging members outside of meetings
Does your organization need help in any of these areas? 

Brittany Florentine
Account Representative, Boardable 
317-689-0990

Check out our new Mobile App, available on both  iOS and  Android devices!

html:
Hi Shawn Micheal​

My name is Katie Cordell and I will be your customer success point of contact moving forward with Boardable. Do you have any questions about your professional account? To kick-off, I’d like to schedule an initial call, during which we will:
  • Review the primary goals you'd like Boardable to help accomplish
  • Help you develop your timeline for rolling out Boardable to your organization
  • Do a quick walkthrough of our platform and answer questions you may have
You can access my calendar to find some time. If you don't see a time that fits your schedule, please let me know so I can give you some other options.

We recently launched a brand new Board Member Academy that I recommend checking out and sharing with your newest board members. The Academy can help new users get started with Boardable as well as including tips and tricks for being an engaged board member.

I look forward to connecting soon!

Best,
Katie

Hi, Shawn.

I've temporarily enabled the professional plan which includes: 
  • Board Packet Quick Print (download/view all agenda documents into one pdf)
  • Reports (export polls, minutes, attendance data, etc.)
  • Unlimited Goals
  • Coming Soon: E-Signatures (will be released end of April)
The professional plan will be automatically disabled on June 30th. If you want to maintain the upgrade at that time there will be an option to purchase the additional features moving forward but you will not be obligated to keep the features. 

We can temporarily delay payment as long as we have a firm deadline. Would delaying payment until July 1st provide some relief? You can issue payment for April, May, June, and July at the juncture. 

Thanks, Samantha

html:
Hi, Shawn.

Thank you so much for being a Boardable customer. We're very grateful for your support and want to reward your passion for the platform by piloting a new referral program with you.

If you refer a new organization to Boardable, you'll get 10% off your Boardable subscription when your referral purchases an annual subscription of their own. (Bonus: The referred organization will also get 10% off.)

To refer another organization, share the following link with your network:

https://app.boardable.com/referred-by/e2e2bf78e91242d16c77d4fb4421661a 

The link is unique to Your 10 Life Foundation, so if any of your contacts use it to become Boardable customers, you'll automatically get credit (and a 10% discount code will be applied to your next bill).

Start the new year in style. Bring Boardable to another worthy organization, and you'll both get an incentive in return.

Please let me know if you have any questions, and thanks again for your business!

Regards,

Ashly

--
Ashly Myers, MBA
Vice President of Revenue and Operations
boardable.com

Hi Katie, 

I have a quick question about the activity log you initially sent me.  If someone simply logs in and either views or downloads a document that was already created, would it have user activity of "Creating or Modifying an Agenda" or would it say something else?  I'm asking because the employee who is listed as modifying documents is claiming she didn't modify anything and simply downloaded stuff.  I don't believe her, so I'm reaching out to you for clarification.  Thanks for any additional support you can provide.

Best Regards,

/s/
Shawn M. Simmerer
Founder & Executive Director

Samantha

We understand is a very challenging of uncertainty and want to be a good partner while you navigate.  How were you hoping we could help? Was there something specific you had in mind?  If your board is continuing to meet virtual, we do have some virtual meeting tools which might also be helpful including a new videoconferencing feature that we are testing with some customers that we could offer free access to at the moment.  Thanks again,  Samantha -- Samantha Alarie-Leca Director of Customer Success  | Boardable p. 317.689.0990  w. boardable.com  Book a 15-minute meeting  | Schedule a strategy session

From: Brittany Florentine <brittany@boardable.com>
Sent: Tuesday, November 5, 2019 8:23 AM
To: Shawn Micheal <Shawn@Your10Life.com>
Subject: Were we not a good fit?
 
Shawn, I see your trial did not have a ton of activity. Is it early in your search?

The hundreds of boards I have worked with, all stress how difficult it is to get board material into the hands of everyone. I work on a committee, and we have 'digitally-duct taped' our own process, but we're all tech-savvy. Not all board members are. Less is best.

The three main reasons organizations switch over to using a board management solution is because they need help: 
1. Centralizing board material
2. Emails are getting out of hand
3. Engaging members outside of meetings
Does your organization need help in any of these areas? 

Brittany Florentine
Account Representative, Boardable 
317-689-0990
